cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use or reference this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "AI-Driven Software Quality Assurance  Research Portfolio"
abstract: >
  Three interconnected Python tools applying AI and Large Language Models
  to software quality assurance: (1) LLM-based automated unit test generation
  using structured prompt engineering (BVA/EP/FBT), (2) software defect
  prediction via MLP, CNN, and self-attention models trained on CK metrics,
  and (3) automated API fault localization using Tarantula, Ochiai, and an
  ML ensemble over test execution traces.
